\ array>set ( array -- set ): one sorted pass (val_cmp) + dedup, O(n log n).
\ Sorts by val_cmp, dedups equal elements, and does not mutate the source array.

\ === ordering and dedup on floats ===
[ 3 1 2 ] array>set . cr                       \ < 1 2 3 >
[ 1 2 3 ] array>set . cr                       \ < 1 2 3 >    already sorted
[ 3 2 1 ] array>set . cr                       \ < 1 2 3 >    reversed
[ ] array>set . cr                             \ < >          empty
[ 5 ] array>set . cr                           \ < 5 >        singleton
[ 7 7 7 7 ] array>set . cr                     \ < 7 >        all duplicates collapse
[ 3 1 2 1 3 2 ] array>set size . cr            \ 3            dedup count
[ -2 0 -5 3 -2 ] array>set . cr                \ < -5 -2 0 3 >  negatives, with a dup

\ === strings sort lexicographically and dedup by content ===
[ "c" "a" "b" "a" ] array>set . cr             \ < "a" "b" "c" >

\ === mixed types sort by tag (symbol < float < string) ===
[ "x" 5 :a ] array>set . cr                    \ < :a 5 "x" >

\ === null (T_NONE) sorts first and dedups ===
[ null 1 null 2 ] array>set size . cr          \ 3            two nulls collapse to one

\ === structural dedup of nested collections ===
[ [ 1 2 ] [ 1 2 ] ] array>set size . cr        \ 1            equal arrays dedup
[ [ 1 2 ] [ 1 3 ] ] array>set size . cr        \ 2            distinct arrays kept
[ < 1 2 > < 2 1 > ] array>set size . cr        \ 1            equal sets dedup

\ === the source array is not mutated ===
[ 3 1 2 ] dup array>set drop . cr              \ [ 3 1 2 ]    original order intact

\ === the result is a genuine set: membership and set ops work ===
[ 3 1 2 ] array>set 2 member? . cr             \ 1
[ 3 1 2 ] array>set 9 member? . cr             \ 0
[ 3 1 2 ] array>set < 2 3 4 > intersection . cr  \ < 2 3 >
[ 3 1 2 1 ] array>set < 1 2 3 > = . cr         \ 1            equal to the set literal

\ === scale: sorts and dedups at size ===
0 9999 range array>set size . cr               \ 10000
0 9999 range reverse array>set 1 take 0 @i . cr  \ 0          smallest first after the sort
0 100 range  0 100 range  concat  array>set size . cr   \ 101  the doubled range dedups

bye
